headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 23, Cavs blast Jazz, improve to 15-2 at home

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris hit a 3-pointer in overtime that put Philadelphia ahead to stay, and Joel Embiid had 28 points, 11 rebounds and four assists as the 76ers extended their winning streak to a season-best five games with a 104-101 win over the struggling...
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris, Embiid carry 76ers past Raptors 104-101 in overtime

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray hit two decisive free throws with 1.3 seconds left, Trae Young had 37 points and 13 assists, and the Atlanta Hawks held off the Orlando Magic 126-125 Monday night to snap their six-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray hits winning free throws, Hawks end Magic's streak

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell had 26 points and the San Antonio Spurs rolled to a 124-105 rout of the Houston Rockets on Monday night to snap a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs rout Rockets 124-105 with 26 from Vassell

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 27 points, 13 rebounds and nine assists to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 116-106 victory on Monday over the unglued Dallas Mavericks, who lost star Luca Doncic and coach Jason Kidd to successive ejections late in the third...
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards leads Timberwolves past flustered Mavericks 116-106

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday frustrated former teammate Zion Williamson like few NBA guards can and drained a momentum-changing, late-game shot for good measure.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's 42 points leads Bucks past Pelicans 128-119

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Just when it appeared it might be “Dame Time,” Shai Gilgeous-Alexander stole the show.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander hits game-winner as Thunder edge Blazers

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — It looked like Father Time might be making some gains on the 37-year-old Chris Paul over the past few months.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul scores season-high 28, Suns roll past Lakers 130-104

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 16 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter and the Charlotte Hornets held off the Sacramento Kings 125-119 on Monday night to stop an eight-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, Oubre lead Hornets past Kings to halt 8-game skid
